WEBVTT

00:00:05.006 --> 00:00:10.553
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:11.178 --> 00:00:14.265
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:15.182 --> 00:00:17.143
At least it is true...

00:00:17.518 --> 00:00:21.272
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:27.278 --> 00:00:28.779
Certainly, thank you.

00:00:35.453 --> 00:00:37.455
Excuse me, let me pass please.

00:00:37.788 --> 00:00:39.707
Raise your glass!

00:00:40.791 --> 00:00:41.917
Please, make way...

00:00:47.298 --> 00:00:48.174
Griffith...

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:56.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

00:01:10.946 --> 00:01:12.907
Griffith!

00:01:33.803 --> 00:01:35.846
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:35.971 --> 00:01:37.723
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:37.932 --> 00:01:41.477
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:41.727 --> 00:01:43.854
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:43.979 --> 00:01:45.940
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:46.065 --> 00:01:48.109
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:48.359 --> 00:01:49.985
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:50.194 --> 00:01:53.614
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:54.323 --> 00:01:57.243
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:58.077 --> 00:01:58.619
<i>I...</i>

00:01:59.078 --> 00:01:59.745
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:59.870 --> 00:02:01.956
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:02:02.081 --> 00:02:02.998
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:03.124 --> 00:02:03.958
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:04.125 --> 00:02:05.751
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:02:05.960 --> 00:02:06.961
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:07.128 --> 00:02:07.878
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:08.003 --> 00:02:09.880
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:02:10.131 --> 00:02:11.048
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:11.173 --> 00:02:12.007
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:12.174 --> 00:02:13.676
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:02:13.926 --> 00:02:15.010
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:15.177 --> 00:02:16.053
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:16.178 --> 00:02:16.929
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:17.012 --> 00:02:18.514
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:23.644 --> 00:02:27.648
Tombstone of Flames

00:02:34.029 --> 00:02:34.947
Griffith!

00:02:35.698 --> 00:02:36.699
Griffith!

00:02:36.824 --> 00:02:37.575
Griffith!

00:02:45.583 --> 00:02:47.835
Sentry, close down the hall!

00:02:48.043 --> 00:02:49.587
Don't allow anyone to leave here!

00:03:03.225 --> 00:03:04.310
Griffith!

00:03:04.476 --> 00:03:05.102
Griffith!

00:03:05.728 --> 00:03:06.979
Griffith!

00:03:19.450 --> 00:03:20.618
It's so easy...

00:03:20.993 --> 00:03:24.622
I've made more money doing this
simple thing than I would have from...

00:03:24.747 --> 00:03:26.498
...ten years of honest work.

00:03:27.499 --> 00:03:29.877
Now, I've got to
leave this city by dawn...

00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:04.286
I never expected that
things would go so smoothly...

00:04:04.411 --> 00:04:06.038
It turned out to be simple.

00:04:06.497 --> 00:04:07.539
Indeed...

00:04:07.665 --> 00:04:11.502
It was very much due to Mr. Foss, and his
handling of the arrangements for our plot.

00:04:11.627 --> 00:04:13.879
It was a great performance, after all.

00:04:14.171 --> 00:04:16.382
No, you're too kind.

00:04:16.882 --> 00:04:19.385
Well done, Minister Foss.

00:04:19.635 --> 00:04:22.096
It is very kind of Your Majesty.

00:04:22.638 --> 00:04:24.014
What's the matter?

00:04:24.098 --> 00:04:25.891
You do not look well.

00:04:26.100 --> 00:04:28.477
M-Maybe it is just your imagination.

00:04:28.727 --> 00:04:30.771
My skin looks sickly under candlelight.

00:04:31.272 --> 00:04:34.858
Anyway, what about
our personal safety?

00:04:35.025 --> 00:04:38.654
Yes, in the worst case
the waiter might be captured...

00:04:38.779 --> 00:04:40.864
...what if he confesses his crimes?

00:04:42.157 --> 00:04:43.993
Our names might be exposed...

00:04:44.660 --> 00:04:47.162
You don't need to worry about that.

00:04:47.663 --> 00:04:50.916
A moment ago, I received a report
from an associate I had in place.

00:04:51.041 --> 00:04:54.169
He already dealt with that matter.

00:04:54.420 --> 00:04:58.048
Oh, there is nothing that
escapes your careful cunning!

00:04:58.173 --> 00:05:00.634
My, you are a quite schemer.

00:05:00.759 --> 00:05:03.012
It's too bad that
you are only a minister.

00:05:03.554 --> 00:05:09.184
Now, allow me to go and
double check on the proceedings.

00:05:24.199 --> 00:05:29.288
At last, dignity will be
restored to the army of Midland.

00:05:29.455 --> 00:05:31.081
That is certain.

00:05:31.206 --> 00:05:35.210
It is ridiculous that a mere mercenary
could become the White Hawk General!

00:05:35.544 --> 00:05:38.213
His example would
put all kinds of ideas...

00:05:38.339 --> 00:05:40.966
...in the heads of the common soldiers.

00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:43.719
I insist that we of noble blood always...

00:05:43.802 --> 00:05:47.681
...have the honor of undertaking pivotal
tasks in our kingdom's administration.

00:05:47.806 --> 00:05:50.100
How could that
man of humble origins...

00:05:50.225 --> 00:05:53.937
Inferior subjects have no
idea how to govern the kingdom!

00:05:54.063 --> 00:05:57.107
Every other country would have
considered us a laughingstock!

00:06:00.486 --> 00:06:03.989
In any case, you all have
toiled for our common goal.

00:06:04.198 --> 00:06:05.574
I must thank you.

00:06:05.741 --> 00:06:07.117
We are unworthy...

00:06:07.242 --> 00:06:10.496
It is you, Your Highness, who
made this possible with your support.

00:06:27.137 --> 00:06:30.015
Finally, the noble
bloodline has been protected.

00:06:40.484 --> 00:06:41.402
W-What?

00:06:41.652 --> 00:06:42.736
Is it smoke?

00:06:42.861 --> 00:06:43.779
That can't be!

00:06:44.655 --> 00:06:45.656
Open the door!

00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:52.246
What's wrong?

00:06:52.371 --> 00:06:53.789
I-It's locked!

00:06:53.914 --> 00:06:54.790
What?

00:06:59.420 --> 00:07:01.004
Step back from the door!

00:07:09.012 --> 00:07:10.180
F-Fire!

00:07:11.181 --> 00:07:12.057
What is this?

00:07:23.819 --> 00:07:25.446
What is this all about?

00:07:41.587 --> 00:07:43.297
G-Griffith!

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:47.718
Why?

00:07:48.051 --> 00:07:51.221
The doctor confirmed
that you had perished!

00:07:53.807 --> 00:07:56.059
Certainly, it appeared that way to you.

00:07:56.185 --> 00:07:57.853
Because I arranged things to that end.

00:07:57.978 --> 00:07:58.604
What?

00:07:59.104 --> 00:08:02.065
What I drank was not a poison.

00:08:02.608 --> 00:08:07.571
I drank a secret medicine compounded
from the essence of Hyoscyamus.

00:08:08.363 --> 00:08:11.825
It put me in a state of apparent death.

00:08:12.201 --> 00:08:14.620
Of course, an
overdose would have killed me...

00:08:15.621 --> 00:08:19.374
However, by risking my life I
was able to trap all of you at once.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:21.502
H-Help me!

00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:26.006
I was just called upon by
the Queen and Minister Foss!

00:08:26.131 --> 00:08:28.509
I had nothing to do with it!

00:08:28.842 --> 00:08:30.260
Hold your tongue, you fool!

00:08:30.761 --> 00:08:32.387
I suppose you are all...

00:08:32.513 --> 00:08:35.641
...used to sitting to the
side and thinking up your little plots.

00:08:37.267 --> 00:08:38.894
This is a war.

00:08:39.186 --> 00:08:41.939
There's nowhere
to sit on the battlefield.

00:08:44.775 --> 00:08:46.401
You swine, Griffith!

00:08:46.568 --> 00:08:48.820
Do you intend to kill me?

00:08:49.321 --> 00:08:51.949
Do you think that a man...

00:08:52.074 --> 00:08:56.703
...of humble origins like you can burn me,
the queen of the Midland, to death?

00:08:57.079 --> 00:08:58.455
I won't allow it!

00:08:58.664 --> 00:09:00.457
I do not admit defeat!

00:09:01.792 --> 00:09:04.836
Death on the battlefield
comes regardless of class...

00:09:04.962 --> 00:09:06.797
...royal, noble or common.

00:09:07.297 --> 00:09:09.174
The loser is fated to die.

00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:29.361
It's all over...

00:09:30.571 --> 00:09:31.989
What's the matter with you?

00:09:32.114 --> 00:09:33.740
You don't look yourself.

00:09:33.865 --> 00:09:37.369
This sort of affair is not such an
unusual event in the court, is it?

00:09:38.453 --> 00:09:39.746
Are you afraid?

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:42.124
Is it because you
betrayed your fellows?

00:09:42.457 --> 00:09:47.379
Perhaps it is because you participated
in murdering the queen of a kingdom?

00:09:50.007 --> 00:09:52.009
I'd like to ask you one thing...

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:57.848
How did Your
Lordship learn about our plot?

00:09:59.016 --> 00:10:00.767
I didn't know about it.

00:10:00.976 --> 00:10:03.145
Then, why did you pick me?

00:10:03.520 --> 00:10:06.773
I predicted you were going
to be my enemy on that morning...

00:10:07.399 --> 00:10:09.359
...before I was last
sent to the battlefield.

00:10:17.534 --> 00:10:18.744
That was when...

00:10:28.754 --> 00:10:30.881
You saw my eyes...

00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:37.137
And since then, I knew you could not
allow me to continue living in the court.

00:10:39.431 --> 00:10:40.891
H-How come you...

00:10:41.808 --> 00:10:46.188
I noticed something familiar in your
eyes at that moment, the taint of fear.

00:10:47.564 --> 00:10:50.942
When a person sees an object
that he finds to be truly fearful...

00:10:51.276 --> 00:10:53.654
...he realizes that it is
impossible to ignore it.

00:10:54.196 --> 00:10:56.948
He has to make a choice...

00:10:57.074 --> 00:11:00.285
...to be subordinate to the
fearful object and hope for protection...

00:11:00.410 --> 00:11:03.705
...or to exterminate that
object to eliminate the fear.

00:11:04.706 --> 00:11:10.420
I knew that there were many people
in the court who were offended by me.

00:11:10.587 --> 00:11:12.964
I couldn't identify who they were...

00:11:13.215 --> 00:11:18.178
However, I was certain that a smart
man like you could find such people...

00:11:18.345 --> 00:11:21.348
...for the purpose of
convincing them to eliminate me.

00:11:23.100 --> 00:11:27.854
However, I never imagined that the
Queen would join in on the intrigue...

00:11:28.438 --> 00:11:31.191
W-What a fine state of affairs!

00:11:31.316 --> 00:11:33.860
His eyes just met mine for a moment!

00:11:34.194 --> 00:11:39.241
Have I been dancing to
his tune ever since then?

00:11:40.575 --> 00:11:43.745
I now know why I can't
stop myself from shivering.

00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:48.375
It is not because I betrayed my fellows,
or took part in the Queen's murder.

00:11:51.086 --> 00:11:52.629
It's because of this man...

00:11:52.838 --> 00:11:55.132
It's because I am afraid of this man!

00:11:58.510 --> 00:12:02.639
This contract sealed with your
blood is no longer of use, is it?

00:12:03.265 --> 00:12:08.270
There should not be any ill will between
us if we are to have a successful future.

00:12:11.773 --> 00:12:15.110
Hopefully, there will
only be peace and friendship.

00:12:18.405 --> 00:12:20.615
Now, come along, Minister...

00:12:20.741 --> 00:12:23.034
I will give something
back to you, as promised.

00:12:23.493 --> 00:12:24.536
Elise!

00:12:24.661 --> 00:12:26.037
Father!

00:12:26.663 --> 00:12:30.500
You are safe now,
don't worry anymore.

00:12:30.667 --> 00:12:32.294
Father!

00:12:34.629 --> 00:12:37.549
That was a touching reunion
between father and daughter.

00:12:38.258 --> 00:12:41.511
Well, it was quite a
job to snatch her up.

00:12:42.512 --> 00:12:46.516
We checked the schedule of that
kid's lessons a week beforehand.

00:12:46.641 --> 00:12:48.810
And as she was leaving in a carriage...

00:12:48.935 --> 00:12:52.063
We courteously looked
after her as you wished.

00:12:52.814 --> 00:12:54.149
You did good job.

00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:55.275
The rest of your reward...

00:12:55.901 --> 00:12:57.027
Oh, great!

00:12:58.653 --> 00:13:02.324
Call us anytime you need something.

00:13:02.699 --> 00:13:07.579
From now on, we only desire
a good relationship with you, sir.

00:13:07.829 --> 00:13:09.831
Well, we are off now.

00:13:19.800 --> 00:13:21.218
What a cinch!

00:13:21.343 --> 00:13:24.721
I've never had such an easy
job, I want to work for him again!

00:13:25.096 --> 00:13:29.726
If he decides he'd rather cut his
connection with us, we'll use blackmail...

00:13:29.851 --> 00:13:32.354
...we've got the goods on him!

00:13:35.482 --> 00:13:36.107
Who is it?

00:13:38.944 --> 00:13:40.237
Who the hell are you?

00:13:57.963 --> 00:13:58.880
It seems to be finished...

00:13:59.381 --> 00:14:00.006
Yeah...

00:14:00.590 --> 00:14:01.883
...it's cleaned up...

00:14:02.133 --> 00:14:02.968
...everything...

00:14:05.762 --> 00:14:10.016
It looked like these men never thought
they'd lose their lives for a few coins.

00:14:11.142 --> 00:14:13.019
Leave the money on them as it was.

00:14:14.104 --> 00:14:17.023
They are clue a share in the profits.

00:14:17.399 --> 00:14:20.652
They did the amount of
work they were paid for.

00:14:21.152 --> 00:14:22.654
Money opens all doors...

00:14:22.779 --> 00:14:23.655
...I see.

00:14:26.157 --> 00:14:28.660
But, is it safe to let that man go?

00:14:29.411 --> 00:14:32.247
He must have learned his
lesson after today's events...

00:14:32.414 --> 00:14:33.164
Maybe...

00:14:33.290 --> 00:14:33.999
Hey...

00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:34.875
Maybe?

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:37.794
If something happens, I'll take
care of it when the time comes.

00:14:38.628 --> 00:14:41.631
Either way, I guess
there will be a serious uproar.

00:14:41.798 --> 00:14:45.427
The Queen and all those others,
so many dead were piled up tonight.

00:14:46.386 --> 00:14:49.681
But no one would imagine that
the man who was supposed to die...

00:14:49.806 --> 00:14:51.308
...was the one pulling the strings.

00:14:53.184 --> 00:14:55.145
Do you think that I am dreadful?

00:14:57.147 --> 00:15:00.150
I had you take part in this entire plot...

00:15:00.775 --> 00:15:03.028
...while never
getting my own hands dirty.

00:15:03.904 --> 00:15:06.823
I left all of the dangerous
and difficult tasks to you alone...

00:15:09.034 --> 00:15:11.328
Do you think that I am a dreadful man?

00:15:14.205 --> 00:15:16.958
You are asking someone who's
already slaughtered a hundred men.

00:15:17.083 --> 00:15:18.460
What's the point of that?

00:15:21.463 --> 00:15:24.591
You're just following this path so
you can realize your dream, right?

00:15:25.175 --> 00:15:26.718
You believe that, don't you?

00:15:27.177 --> 00:15:29.304
So, what's all this
you're talking about now?

00:15:30.972 --> 00:15:32.182
You're right...

00:15:32.557 --> 00:15:34.225
Now, let's go back!

00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:37.062
A dead man like you
shouldn't hang around here all night.

00:15:37.604 --> 00:15:40.815
You've got to stop Caska and everyone
else from worrying about you too much.

00:15:40.982 --> 00:15:41.733
Yeah...

00:15:42.734 --> 00:15:48.073
You didn't notice that Caska put on a
dress for the celebration where you died?

00:15:48.198 --> 00:15:49.115
Really?

00:15:49.366 --> 00:15:51.493
She's quite attractive to see...

00:16:06.132 --> 00:16:06.967
Gri...

00:16:07.258 --> 00:16:08.259
...ffith ...

00:16:13.515 --> 00:16:15.016
Griffith!

00:16:17.268 --> 00:16:18.103
Griffith!

00:16:20.981 --> 00:16:22.399
Are you all right?

00:16:25.026 --> 00:16:27.487
Griffith, Griffith...

00:16:29.614 --> 00:16:32.033
I'm sorry I worried you, Caska.

00:16:32.492 --> 00:16:34.619
We were so scared
about what happened to you.

00:16:34.786 --> 00:16:39.124
Ever since you passed out,
Caska has been in a state of shock.

00:16:40.166 --> 00:16:41.501
I am sorry.

00:16:44.754 --> 00:16:46.631
You look pretty in that dress.

00:17:30.675 --> 00:17:34.554
Just as the Chuder Empire
acquiesced to an armistice signing...

00:17:34.763 --> 00:17:36.306
Who on earth did this?

00:17:36.681 --> 00:17:40.018
Perhaps, someone who is
plotting against the armistice signing.

00:17:40.310 --> 00:17:42.562
It must be reactionaries from Chuder!

00:17:42.771 --> 00:17:46.649
Otherwise, there is the possibility of
an assassin sent by a third country.

00:17:46.775 --> 00:17:48.276
How foolish they are...

00:17:48.777 --> 00:17:52.530
It is quite unforgivable to
disturb our long-waited peace...

00:20:04.329 --> 00:20:05.413
Snow...

00:20:14.088 --> 00:20:15.089
Guts...

00:20:23.723 --> 00:20:26.726
And the woman was quite a character!

00:20:27.352 --> 00:20:30.480
Caska, where are you going this late?

00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:33.608
What's the use of being in such a hurry?

00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:36.945
She's probably just going to the
bathroom, since it's so cold tonight...

00:20:44.452 --> 00:20:45.370
Guts!

00:20:53.628 --> 00:20:54.504
Guts...

00:20:55.004 --> 00:20:55.964
You're...

00:20:57.340 --> 00:20:59.384
Are you leaving?

00:21:00.760 --> 00:21:01.886
Are you?

00:21:03.638 --> 00:21:05.014
Wait a minute.

00:21:05.598 --> 00:21:08.142
You and I don't get along, but...

00:21:08.518 --> 00:21:11.020
I mean, we have
risked our lives together.

00:21:11.854 --> 00:21:15.900
All the hard work we
endured as Hawks is bearing fruit.

00:21:16.401 --> 00:21:18.403
And this is just the beginning, isn't it?

00:21:18.861 --> 00:21:20.530
But despite that...

00:21:21.030 --> 00:21:23.783
I've already decided.

00:21:24.409 --> 00:21:25.368
But...

00:21:26.286 --> 00:21:27.412
I don't...

00:21:29.789 --> 00:21:33.793
I don't want to live like
this, buried in his dream...

00:22:02.905 --> 00:22:05.033
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.703
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:12.707
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:15.710
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.420 --> 00:22:18.963
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.088 --> 00:22:20.214
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.426
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.677 --> 00:22:27.597
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:30.933
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.225 --> 00:22:34.562
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.979 --> 00:22:37.857
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.608 --> 00:22:41.611
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.487 --> 00:22:45.239
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:46.240 --> 00:22:49.118
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:49.994 --> 00:22:51.829
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:10.264 --> 00:23:11.265
Separation.

00:23:12.100 --> 00:23:16.270
It is unavoidable for anyone
